'''Ethics''' (from Greek ''[[ethos|ἦθος]]'' meaning "custom") is the branch of [[axiology]], one of the four major branches of [[philosophy]], which attempts to understand the nature of [[morality]]; to distinguish that which is [[right]] from that which is [[wrong]]. The [[Western philosophy|Western tradition]] of ethics is sometimes called '''moral philosophy'''. Ethics in plain words means studying and analyzing right from wrong.
